          </p>

          <div class="bg-blue-50 border-l-4 border-blue-600 p-6 mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Technology Overview</h2>
            <p>S-VIDIA's Flexible Delta Compression (FDC) technology records only changes and movement in video while retaining frames as separate images. With no hardware compression, the system stores exact camera images in full quality, providing 60% less recording space compared to conventional systems while maintaining court-admissible evidence quality.</p>
          </div>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">The Evolution of Surveillance Technology</h2>
          
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">Traditional Surveillance Limitations</h3>
          <p class="mb-4">
            For decades, security cameras faced fundamental trade-offs:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-6 space-y-2">
            <li><strong>Quality vs Storage:</strong> High-resolution video consumed massive storage</li>
            <li><strong>Coverage vs Cost:</strong> More cameras meant exponentially higher costs</li>
            <li><strong>Recording vs Bandwidth:</strong> Remote viewing required significant internet speeds</li>
            <li><strong>Detection vs False Alarms:</strong> Motion sensors triggered countless false alerts</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">The S-VIDIA Flexible Delta Compression (FDC)</h3>
          <p class="mb-4">
            S-VIDIA's mission is clear: "The future of this compression method lies in the hands of those who demand quality." Their FDC technology addresses every traditional limitation through innovative engineering:
          </p>

          <div class="bg-green-50 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
            <h4 class="font-bold mb-3">Core FDC Features:</h4>
            <ul class="space-y-2">
              <li>✓ <strong>Delta Recording:</strong> Records only changes/movement in video</li>
              <li>✓ <strong>No Hardware Compression:</strong> Stores exact camera images in full quality</li>
              <li>✓ <strong>Superior Bandwidth Efficiency:</strong> Significantly reduced bandwidth requirements</li>
              <li>✓ <strong>Military-Grade Security:</strong> 128-bit encrypted connections</li>
              <li>✓ <strong>Real-Time Analysis:</strong> Raw video analysis and automated movement search</li>
